cd : to the project path
git status :  to check the project status
git init : It will initialize the folder as git repo
git add -A :  to add project ALL files at once to git repo in staging env (git initialise) to track untrack files
git reset : to move the files out of the staging area again
touch .gitignore : it will create gitignore file to put the folder files which is not required to track or add to stating
ls -la : the gitingore file will be available there now by the name .gitignore
we can ignore .log, pycache and .idea

to edit the gitignore file from terminal we use  vi .gitignore
to get back  : first press esc and type ':x' and hit enter

if we want to commit to local repo
git commit -m "This is my first commit, any comments here"





